<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880419-0190 </DOCNO><HL> Britain Posts March Retail Sales </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EUROP </CO><DATELINE> LONDON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Seasonally adjusted retail sales in Britain, calculated on a volume basis, rose 7.1% in March from a year earlier but fell 0.3% from February, according to provisional data released by the Department of Trade and Industry.    Sales value rose about 11% in March from a year earlier, the department said. </TEXT></DOC>